<TEXT>
andrew youngs campaign to become the nations 
second black elected governor has run into a pair of obstacles 
slow fund raising and claims by his chief democratic primary foe 
that he is soft on crime 
the former atlanta mayor seeking to repeat in georgia what l 
douglas wilder did last year in virginia has attempted to avoid 
race as an issue 
recently he said voters at a campaign stop asked if he thought 
the state was ready for a black governor 
i said that when the university of georgia was ready to be 
no 1 in football they didnt care what color herschel walker was 
they just wanted to know could the big dog run young said 
and i said im about as close as youre going to get to herschel 
walker in politics 
youngs major opponent lt gov zell miller has attacked him 
as soft on crime miller cites fbi statistics that showed atlanta 
was the nations bigcity crime capital during the last two years 
of youngs eightyear tenure 
young left the mayors office in january he served in congress 
from 197377 and was president carters un ambassador after that 
young and miller the states no 2 official for the past 16 
years are the frontrunners in a contest that includes former gov 
lester maddox and two state legislators 
the primary is july 17 with a runoff aug 7 if no candidate 
wins a majority the democratic nominee will face the winner of a 
republican primary contest most likely state rep johnny isakson 
gov joe frank harris a democrat is completing his second term 
and cannot seek reelection 
miller had raised 276 million through april 3 according to 
disclosure reports and his campaign is believed to be the 
wealthiest 
young has not yet filed a disclosure report he has said he is 
struggling to raise money from local businesses and has raised only 
about 1 million overall 
young said the crime statistics cited by miller were skewed by a 
change in the reporting of crime information and other factors 
miller who has proposed marine corpstype boot camps for young 
first offenders and other lawandorder measures called the 
response a dodge 
this election is going to boil down to a choice between andy 
young who wants to run from the crime and drug problem and zell 
miller who wants to run right at it miller declared 
but franklin o greer youngs consultant predicted millers 
strategy would fail 
zell just wants to point fingers people dont think thats a 
fair attack said greer who helped manage wilders successful 
campaign in virginia 
maxine goldstein vice chairwoman of the state democratic party 
said she has not heard crime discussed as an issue in the rural 
middle part of georgia 
the whole focus of his crime control effort was atlanta for 
people down here i dont think thats as strong as it would be in 
the metro area she said 
added rep larry walker democratic leader of the state house of 
representatives race is not the issue it once was 
but emory university political science professor merle black 
who studies southern politics said the fact that georgia has a 
larger black population than virginia 27 percent to 17 percent 
will not necessarily work to youngs advantage 
what weve found in the past is as long as blacks remain a 
minority as the black share of the population goes up you do have 
an intensification of color consciousness on the part of whites 
black said 
for example he said george wallaces 1968 presidential 
campaign did best in rural southern areas with substantial black 
populations and wallace was obviously not drawing votes from 
blacks 
youngs platform stresses economic development for rural areas 
where he hopes to recruit white voters 
