<TEXT>
john kelly the us official whom lebanese 
kidnappers want to deal with spent two turbulent years as 
ambassador to that country during which he was shot at by 
christian gunmen and once was reprimanded for his role in the 
irancontra affair 
a possible deal to release an american held hostage in lebanon 
may have fallen apart this week over president bushs refusal to 
have kelly get involved 
islamic jihad for the liberation of palestine a proiranian 
group believed to be holding three american educators hostage 
demanded that kelly fly to damascus to coordinate some final 
steps in the release of a hostage 
but bush refused saying the united states does not knuckle 
under to demands 
kelly 50 is a career foreign service officer who worked in 
obscurity until president reagan sent him to lebanon as us 
ambassador in 1986 
he quickly found himself involved in back channel 
discussions with the white house on secret negotiations for the 
release of americans held hostage 
kelly consulted with robert mcfarlane the presidents national 
security adviser john poindexter the successor to mcfarlane 
oliver l north a national security council aide and richard v 
secord a retired air force general who was in the arms business 
mcfarlane poindexter north and secord all have been convicted 
of crimes arising from the us sale of weapons to iran and the 
diversion of profits to the contra rebels in nicaragua 
the discussions involving kelly were so secret that even 
secretary of state george shultz was kept in the dark about them 
and when shultz found out he was shocked that kelly had 
discussed the hostages and the use of arms sales as an 
inducement to win their release 
shultz summoned kelly to washington to reprimand him in person 
for dealing behind the secretarys back the state department said 
kelly did not take part in unauthorized negotiations for the 
release of the hostages 
kelly was described at the time as a bythebook diplomat 
who may have been under orders not to inform the state department 
of his activities 
in 1988 kellys bulletproof limousine was hit by gunfire in a 
brief shooting exchange between his bodyguards and a christian 
militia patrol in east beirut he was not hurt but less than four 
months later he left the country because of a heart ailment 
