likely 2 percent increase in annual milk production the report 
said although a surge in cheese sales would not be 
unprecedented it has rarely occurred 
consumer prices of dairy products as a group in early 1990 rose 
more than 10 percent from a year earlier greatly exceeding the 
overall increases in retail food and consumer prices 
retail dairy prices probably will trend down in coming months 
although any signs of strength in wholesale prices will tend to 
lessen and delay retail price declines the report said 
