estonians rescind a declaration that their republic is an occupied 
independent state 
the soviets have imposed an energy embargo on lithuania which 
declared independence march 11 
estonian and latvia have not formally declared independence but 
have said they want to pursue it 
gorbachev reportedly told their leaders the republics could 
belong to a confederation which could imply a major concession 
because the russian word is used for a loosely allied organization 
like the british commonwealth 
gorbachev previously spoke only of a federation like the 
united states where the states have specific powers but the 
national government is strong 
however gorbachev did not define what he meant by 
confederation lippma said 
lippma reported in a telephone interview that gorbachev said 
if some kind of blockade has to be imposed part of the 
population might get very angry and there would be bloodshed and 
in that case he would impose presidential rule 
and then we would find out what occupation really is lippma 
added 
presidential rule can include martial law and suspension of 
parliament 
lippma said president arnold ruutel of estonia likely will heed 
gorbachevs request that parliament formally reconsider the 
estonian declaration probably on monday however he said a 
reversal was very unlikely 
we have no clearcut commitment of what we would get in return 
if we canceled it he said so estonia and lithuania are very 
much in the same boat 
similarly gorbachev told president anatoly gorbunov of latvia 
and his delegation that he would not talk further if they declare 
independence on may 3 as planned said aris yansons gorbunovs 
assistant 
gorbachev has said he believes disintegration of the soviet 
union would lead to great ethnic violence but that danger is 
considered more likely in the volatile south than in the baltic 
region 
gorbachevs tone with the latvians was highly critical said 
raimons lochmelis of the information office of the latvian peoples 
