in the past most palestinians have stayed home during strikes 
often making them calmer than other days in the occupied 
territories 
during todays strike which coincided with the final friday of 
the moslem fasting month of ramadan the islamic fundamentalist 
movement hamas or zeal allowed taxis and buses to operate so they 
could carry moslems to prayer services the strike also closed 
businesses in arab east jerusalem 
the call for tactical changes in the revolt against israeli 
occupation came in a leaflet issued thursday by the unified 
leadership of the uprising 
among the new tactics is a call for palestinians to turn out 
their lights for 15 minutes on may 5 to protest the continued 
closure of palestinian universities on april 28 drivers were 
asked to halt their vehicles and honk their horns for five minutes 
to show solidarity with arabs deported by israel 
new modes of protest had been demanded by the marxist popular 
front for the liberation of palestine which accused the united 
leadership of complacency and threatened to break away the marxist 
front and other factions of the palestine liberation organization 
which back the leadership issued a joint statement earlier this 
week promising a change in tactics 
the latest leaflet also called for new controls in dealing with 
palestinians suspected of collaborating with israel 
at least 207 palestinians have been killed by fellow arabs since 
the start of the uprising most on suspicion of informing on 
uprising activists the leaflet said collaborators should be 
ostracized socially but there should be no killings without 
special orders issued by highranking circles 
aside from the collaborator deaths israeli soldiers or 
civilians have killed 674 palestinians in the uprising and 43 
israelis have died 
</TEXT>
