lech walesa won an overwhelming vote of 
confidence from solidarity at the unions second national congress 
today after delivering an impassioned defense of his 10 years as 
the movements leader 
on the congress second day and just 24 hours before an expected 
reelection bid walesa asked for a show of support delegates 
present responded with a vote of 357 in favor one against and 22 
abstentions 
walesas earlier impromptu address highlighted internal tensions 
in the movement that weathered repression and toppled the communist 
government since it last met as a whole in 1981 
the victory i am giving to you the mistakes are ours but 
all the mistakes we made you should correct here and today he 
said 
i did this only for poland not for myself it was our 
mutual victory i was only the driver 
walesa still immensely important in poland despite some 
slippage in popularity polls accepted the vote of confidence with 
his arms extended in the traditional solidarity v for victory 
the crowd chanted the fond diminutive of his first name 
lechu lechu lechu 
walesa is to run for reelection as union chairman saturday he 
was likely to retain control of solidarity as it struggles to 
decide how much of a union and how much of a political force it 
will be in postcommunist poland 
parliament member andrzej malachowski appealed to fellow 
delegates to end intrigue saying stop it please lech walesa 
has well served the fatherland 
