jailings of its leaders and thousands of supporters confiscation 
of equipment and public attacks by communist authorities 
even as it faces deep questions about its future solidarity 
launched the congress thursday celebrating its triumphs present 
for the first day was prime minister tadeusz mazowiecki once 
imprisoned for his solidarity activism 
the union regained legal status only on april 17 1989 then 
after the june elections took control of the government 
but solidarity has managed to sign up only 22 million of the 10 
million members it had in 1981 opinion polls show confidence 
dropping as the public undergoes economic hardships associated with 
the strict austerity program being pursued by the 
solidaritycreated government 
economic restructuring is forcing plant closures and raising 
unemployment among the industrial workers who comprise the backbone 
of solidarity 
the delegates are expected to debate how much they want 
solidarity to be confined to union issues decide whether to create 
a solidaritylinked political party and draw up a union program 
before the congress closes tuesday 
