the process of shipping damaged nuclear 
fuel from the three mile island reactor to the us energy 
departments idaho national engineering laboratory is completed 
officials at tmi said the final shipment 20 canisters packed in 
three specially designed rail shipping casks arrived at the 
laboratory thursday 
since july 1986 300000 pounds of fuel and debris were shipped 
by rail from tmi to idaho falls in 22 trips the operation cost the 
plant operator gpu nuclear corp 23 million said spokeswoman 
mary wells 
scientists at the laboratory are studying the fuel to better 
understand the effects of the march 1979 accident at three mile 
island in which a combination of mechanical and operator errors 
allowed the radioactive core to overheat and partially melt 
workers are continuing to decontaminate the plant and gpu 
