an inquiry by city college into the limits of academic freedom the 
new york times reported in todays editions 
the schools student body is 39 percent black 28 percent 
hispanic 17 percent white and 16 percent asian 
the white teacher michael levin a professor of philosophy has 
written at least three articles for academic journals contending 
that it has been amply confirmed over the last several decades 
that on average blacks are significantly less intelligent than 
whites the times said 
levin has argued that a deficiency in intelligence rather than 
discrimination or poverty accounts for the underrepresentation of 
blacks in fields like medicine engineering and philosophy the 
times said levin holds a doctorate in philosophy 
the black professor leonard jeffries jr chairman of the black 
studies department calls people of european ancestry the ice 
