<TEXT>
the senate agriculture committee responded to 
concerns about global warming friday by including a forestry 
section in a farm bill for the first time 
in light of the numerous issues that have developed pertaining 
to forestry global warming timber production threatened and 
endangered species air and water quality it is time we 
reexamine our commitment to state and private forestry and the 
numerous owners of small private forests said sen wyche 
fowler dga 
fowler is chairman of the subcommittee on conservation and 
forests and comes from a state where small privately held forest 
acreage generates about 9 billion and provides 80000 jobs 
including forestry in the farm bill underscores an important 
fact said sen patrick leahy dvt chairman of the agriculture 
committee the total value of our timber harvests exceeds that of 
any crop including corn soybeans wheat and hay 
about half the timber used commercially in the united states 
comes from the 482 million acres of private forests most of which 
grow wild about 21 million acres are managed to assure certain 
timber supplies are available 
the national forests which supply the rest of the nations 
timber are carefully managed by the federal government 
leahy said one goal of the legislation is to put another 25 
million acres of private forestland under management programs 
the bill which will be in the version of the 1990 farm bill 
that goes to the full senate makes the most significant changes in 
forestry laws in 14 years 
it would 
set up a publicprivate partnership with 8 million private 
forest owners so the private sector could get technical assistance 
already available to government foresters 
establish an easement program through which the government 
would buy development rights from forest owners to assure that 
environmentally sensitive forestlands arent threatened by 
commercial building 
create federal state and local coordination committees to help 
carry out the programs offered by the bill 
money for the programs would be determined later 
the house has not acted on any similar legislation in the 
version of the farm bill it is writing 
