percent from a year ago and 4 percent more than two years ago the 
agriculture department said friday 
officials said it was the largest april 1 feedlot inventory of 
cattle since 1978 nebraska was no 1 edging texas the usual 
leader 
increases from a year ago were reported in iowa kansas 
nebraska oklahoma and washington california and minnesota were 
unchanged decreases were reported for arizona colorado idaho 
illinois south dakota and texas 
marketings of fed cattle for slaughter during january february 
and march totaled 558 million head down 1 percent from the same 
period of 1989 and 5 percent below 1988 the report said 
the placement of new cattle and calves on feed during the first 
quarter of the year totaled 609 million head down 2 percent from 
1989 but 5 percent more than in 1988 
cattle feeders indicated they expect to market 609 million head 
during april may and june up 1 percent from last years second 
quarter and 4 percent more than in 1988 the report said it would 
also be the same number as feedlot placements in the first quarter 
state feedlot cattle inventories are listed here for the 13 
states which account for about 85 percent of the nations beef 
the first number is the number of cattle in thousands as of april 
1 and the second number is the percentage of a year earlier 
