intentions in vietnam and discussed us bases overseas 
vietnam foreign minister nguyen co thach told the delegation 
that all soviet troops would be out of vietnam by 1992 schroeder 
said in the 44page report this is good news 
the soviet union moved into the usbuilt base at cam ranh bay 
at the conclusion of the vietnam war in 1975 but pentagon 
officials said in january that the soviets had withdrawn some 
fighter planes and bombers 
in an interview with reporters schroeder said the soviets no 
longer are basing their planned withdrawal from cam rahn bay on 
whether the united states remains at the subic naval base in the 
philippines as they have said previously 
leases on six us installations in the philippines expire in 
1991 and american officials anticipate difficult negotiations for 
continued base rights there 
