<TEXT>
some 25000 compact pickup trucks converted 
into small motorhomes have a defect that could cause their rear 
wheels to come off according to federal highway safety officials 
who plan a hearing on the problem 
in the first such action in six years involving a vehicle on 
us roads the national highway traffic safety administration 
upgraded a 2yearold defects investigation into an initial 
determination that a safety defect exists 
the action taken earlier this week could lead to a recall but 
none has yet been ordered said nhtsa spokesman tim hurd on friday 
manufacturers usually issue recalls on their own before the 
government forces the issue but the motorhomes are built by 30 
different companies he said 
the last step before a recall order will be a public meeting may 
23 in washington at which anyone may testify 
the agency determined that the motorhomes have overloaded rear 
axles which can cause failure of wheel bearings or axle shafts and 
result in the vehicles wheels coming off 
the vehicles have prompted 440 reports of problems including 16 
accidents with injuries and 63 instances in which wheels fell off 
the axles according to george reagle nhtsa associate 
administrator for enforcement 
the small motorhomes are nearly all modified versions of toyota 
minipickup trucks with double wheels installed in the rear about 
25000 were sold between 1977 and 1986 nhtsa said 
reagle warned owners of the homes to take precautions until the 
issue is settled 
he recommended that they avoid unbalanced loads minimize weight 
on the rear axle keep water tanks nearly empty while traveling 
and avoid towing anything or using a roof rack 
tire pressure should be checked frequently with inside tires at 
a slightly higher pressure than those on the outside he said also 
recommending that rear wheel bearings be inspected every 10000 
miles and that a competent mechanic be asked to inspect the whole 
rear axle and rear suspension 
the 30 manufacturers of the units identified by nhtsa are blue 
marlin coachman damon esquire ez rider four seasons 
gardnerpacific granville huntsman keystone leisure odyssey 
odyssey mirage of elkhart monterey leisure national rv dolphin 
and seabreeze new horizon new world perris valley campers 
ranger rbr rockwood saddleback sandtana shasta sunland 
express sunline sunrader travette voyager and western rv 
