wines withheld from sale after discovering unacceptably high levels 
of a sweetener in them 
the ministry of agriculture fisheries and food said scientists 
found unacceptable levels of sorbitol a sweetener found naturally 
in apple or pear juice but banned from wine because it can change 
the flavor 
the wine standards board which enforces european community 
regulations ordered the 14 wines to be withheld while more tests 
were carried out said a ministry spokesman who by custom was not 
identified 
the ministry is acting to safeguard the integrity of wine the 
presence of sorbitol suggests that fruit juice was added in making 
the wine or that sorbitol was added said the spokesman 
local authorities have also been asked to carry out checks to 
see if stocks in stores broke the rules the spokesman said 
chile is the largest south american exporter of wine to britain 
selling 2 million bottles a year according to the wine and spirits 
association 
