whip up antinea hysteria and suggested that he pay attention to 
the commandment against bearing false witness 
frohnmayer said the illinois art exhibit grant was made before 
congress banned federal support for obscene art in any case he 
said wildmon was wrong to suggest that the nea is a purveyor of 
pornography or is somehow out of control 
the endowment an independent federal agency with a budget of 
1713 million supports a wide variety of artists and artistic 
institutions with taxpaid grants that must be matched by private 
donors 
the nea has been the target of attacks by conservative lawmakers 
led by sen jesse helms rnc and rep dana rohrabacher 
rcalif since last summer for its support for exhibits of 
controversial works by photographer robert mapplethorpe and artist 
andres serrano 
last fall congress voted to forbid nea financing of art that 
may be considered obscene and without serious literary 
artistic political or scientific value 
the lawmakers also ordered a special commission created to 
review the neas grantmaking procedures and withheld 45000 from 
the nea as a penalty for supporting the mapplethorpe and serrano 
exhibits 
officials of people for the american way action fund which 
describes itself as a constitutional liberties organization 
fighting censorship said their poll showed that the public 
overwhelmingly opposes censorship of controversial art even if 
they find it personally offensive 
the poll was conducted for the group by research amp forecasts 
inc of new york which conducted random telephone surveys of 1200 
adults in late march 
the firm said the poll showed that 68 percent of the public 
supports federal financing of the arts and that only 30 percent 
agrees that government funding to avant garde or leadingedge 
artists should be stopped because a few people feel their work is 
controversial 
the poll takers said 81 percent of those surveyed agreed that 
congress should not pass laws that interfere with our rights to 
free expression they said 93 percent agreed that even if i 
find a particular piece of art objectionable others have the right 
to view it 
of those surveyed they said 61 percent take the neas side in 
favoring the current system of having citizen panels make grant 
decisions only 13 percent they said supported helms efforts to 
slash funds and tighten controls over the endowment 
sen edward m kennedy dmass hailed the poll results as a 
welcome vote of confidence in the arts endowment and proof that 
americans reject the knownothing censorship the right wing is 
