settler group said even though the court treated the case as a 
simple tenancy dispute it was a political confrontation 
the motives of all sides are political this is a struggle 
over the rights of jews to live everywhere in jerusalem he told 
the associated press 
this is one of the most sensitive places in the world 
avraham sochovolsky attorney for the church told the threejudge 
panel there is no quiet moment there now we have to douse this 
fire 
