the company of gerald v bull the us 
rocket scientist who was mysteriously slain at his brussels 
apartment last month will be going out of business his family 
said thursday 
it denied the firm space research corp was linked to shipping 
steel tubes from britain to iraq that british officials say can be 
made into the barrel of a giant gun 
the bull family has decided to cease all src operations and 
dissolve companies within the src group the company said in a 
brief statement the bull family contests to be or to have been 
involved in any illegal acts or arms traffic of any nature 
bull 62 a canadianborn american was an aerospace scientist 
and reputed to be an artillery expert he was slain march 22 his 
killer remains at large 
british customs officials seized eight steel tube sections on 
april 12 as they were about to be shipped to iraq the manufacturer 
has denied the tubes can be used as a gun barrel 
police have ruled out robbery as a motive in bulls slaying 
they said they found 20000 in the victims pockets 
bull built a 6000acre compound for his space research corp in 
north troy vt on the canadian border in the late 1970s 
he moved src to brussels in 1980 after serving a sixmonth term 
for selling howitzer technology to south africa in violation of a 
us law and a united nations arms embargo 
