at least 300 people were killed in political 
violence in the first half of april the bloodiest 15day period in 
perus decadelong guerrilla war according to a senate commission 
sen enrique bernales of the socialist left coalition said 
thursday the guerrillas launched 178 attacks against government and 
civilian targets in the same period also a record 
much of the violence occurred before the april 8 general 
elections rebels tried to sabotage the elections by assassinating 
candidates and threatening to kill people who voted 
perus elected government is currently battling two violent 
leftist insurgencies 
the most radical group is the maoinspired shining path which 
began fighting 10 years ago in the southern andean highlands it 
now operates throughout the andes and in the cocaproducing jungles 
of the northeast 
the tupac amaru revolutionary movement is a smaller and less 
violent group that operates mainly in lima and some regions of the 
northern jungle the procuban group took up arms in 1984 
bernales head of a respected senate commission on violence 
said 150 of the april deaths were confirmed by the military or 
police the rest were unofficial reports received by his office 
more than 18000 people have been killed since 1980 he said a 
great majority of the dead were civilians killed by both sides 
bernales criticized president alan garcias government for 
telling the public it is winning the war against the guerrillas 
this is dramatic evidence that terrorism has not been slowed 
but has increased bernales said 
the highest monthly death toll was recorded by the commission 
last june when 470 people were killed 
