the hottest investment in tokyo this year is cash 
with uncertainty reigning over japans stock and bond markets 
and us treasury bond prices tumbling many investment managers 
have sought shelter for their funds 
they are finding it in tokyos overnight money markets 
shortterm certificates of deposit and other interestbearing cash 
investments brokers and analysts say 
true this weeks rebound in the yen and in stock prices have 
led some analysts to believe the bear market might be over but 
they have not washed away the caution 
people are hiding in cash and cds from all of the unpleasant 
possibilities said william h brown president the investment 
advisory firm of scudder stevens and clark overseas 
the rate for unsecured overnight call loans the shortestterm 
cash investment has been above 7 percent recently thats less 
than a quarter percentage point below the yield on the benchmark 
10year japanese government bond 
whats more threemonth certificates of deposit have been 
quoted on the open market this week at more than 75 percent 
such high rates offer investors a rewarding hedge for their 
money while market turbulence continues 
who wants to be the first to stick out their neck by taking a 
stand when you can get those kinds of rates on the overnight 
calls said one dealer who spoke on the condition she not be 
identified 
