economy with its relatively stable prices justifies according to 
the bank of japan 
the broad money supply which includes shortterm instruments 
rose 117 percent from january through march the central bank 
reported this week in that period the stock market has lost a 
quarter of its value the yen has fallen more than 10 percent 
against the dollar and government bond prices have dropped to 
about 85 percent of their face value 
the central bank had forecast only a 9 percent expansion of the 
money supply for the quarter bank of japan officials said a major 
cause of the excessive growth was the merrygoround of 
funds slushing through cash instruments as investors darted in and 
out of various markets 
the cash glut shows no sign of abating the central bank now 
predicts 11 percent money growth for the marchmay quarter that 
could trigger a viscious spiral if fast money growth further erodes 
the yens value 
it means more inflation and that will result in higher 
interest rates whether the boj does anything about it or not 
