a widespread recession thats because so much of the economy is 
based on service industries that dont have big credit needs he 
says 
stricter lending also may reduce pressure on the fed to raise 
interest rates to stem inflationary pressures that pressure heated 
up last week with reports showing that inflation ran at an 85 
percent rate in the first quarter an eightyear high while 
industrial production surged 
they dont have to raise interest rates to prevent credit 
extensionbecause its not happening anyway fabbri says of the 
fed 
this should eventually lessen inflation pressure and help 
reduce domestic demand for foreign goods 
