<DOCNO> AP900420-0235 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
fashion is losing to flora and fauna with a 
house vote to ban strip mining the scenic beds of new mexicos 
jemez river for the pumice used in making stonewashed jeans 
a bill approved 3911 on thursday would put the 11 miles of 
the east fork of the river under the protection of the national 
wild and scenic rivers systems 
it also protects 205 miles of the pecos river from anyone who 
would permanently change the contours of the land such as in the 
stripmining of block pumice used by jeans manufacturers 
the section of the jemez river being protected features rugged 
canyons thick forests lush meadows and is a popular trout stream 
that also provides a habitat for the unique jemez mountain 
salamander 
the segment of the pecos river is known for granite canyons 
waterfalls and mountain meadows 
we had a legislative proposal to designate the rivers and at 
the same time we had a regulatory action going forth on a mining 
claim said rep bruce vento dminn who sponsored the bill 
with reps bill richardson dnm and steven schiff rnm 
in a very real sense the east fork of the jemez river was the 
nations first river threatened by stonewashed jeans richardson 
said 
vento said the mining would substantially change the surfaces 
around the river 
congress has a right to designate the river and prevent this 
type of misuse or abuse he said 
the mining claims in question within the proposed jemez river 
corridor are for pumice a material used in the manufacture of 
stonewashed jeans said rep nick joe rahall ii dwva 
for my part i would forego the jeans in order to preserve the 
environmental values of the river he said 
the bill would allow existing claimholders to mine land in the 
river corridors but maintains the land as federal property it 
would require that after mining claimholders return the area to 
its natural condition 
the measure would prohibit the sale of mining patents under the 
federal 1872 mining laws used by speculators looking for valuable 
minerals 
the block pumice found in rich quantities along the river is 
considered a valuable mineral because it is difficult to find its 
largest market is in the manufacturing of stonewashed blue jeans 
said a house interior committee staffer 
the bill is supported by the administration similar legislation 
already has passed the senate 
</TEXT>
