the contract for may delivery of west texas intermediate the 
benchmark grade of us crude oil slipped 11 cents per 42gallon 
barrel to settle at 1795 on thursday the contract jumped 110 
to 1806 
the may contract expired friday most other contract months 
showed smaller declines 
crude prices rallied thursday after word spread that a special 
session of the organization of petroleum exporting countries 
eightmember monitoring panel would meet may 2 in geneva 
switzerland 
the market was anticipating cutbacks in opecs overproduction 
analysts said 
oil analysts estimate the 13nation cartel is pumping more than 
24 million barrels of crude a day well over its ceiling of 221 
million barrels a day for the first half of the year 
chris gohler an analyst at elders futures inc said the rally 
continued into friday morning but later tapered off as the effects 
of the opec news faded 
refined petroleum products traded on the exchange were mixed 
the contract for may delivery of wholesale unleaded gasoline 
rose 015 cent to settle at 6193 cents a gallon other contract 
months posted larger gains with the june contract advancing 032 
cent to 6093 
