governor has opposed the merger claiming it would be 
anticompetitive 
at scecorps annual meeting thursday a shareholder suggested 
van de kamps motives were political causing chairman howard allen 
to erupt in anger 
you said it i didnt but i agree with you 100 percent 
said allen 
im just so disgusted with it i thought he had a higher sense 
of intellectual honesty and competence and ill tell you it really 
infuriated me as you can tell 
so angry was allen that another shareholder stepped up to the 
microphone to chastise him 
you have a duty to hold your temper back the shareholder 
said 
allen retorted youre entitled to your opinion and im 
entitled to mine and i thank you very much 
the merger is the subject of federal hearings under way in 
washington and also needs approval by the state public utilities 
commission which has scheduled hearings later this year 
allen said he was confident the deal would be approved by the 
end of the year but he acknowledged opposition from some san diego 
residents fearful of losing a utility with local headquarters 
the merger calls for scecorp to trade stock for sdgampe rather 
than pay cash the combined company would have 48 million 
customers 
scecorp contends the merger will result in far lower rates for 
utility users throughout its area but the staff of the puc has 
opposed the merger saying there is no guarantee rates would be 
lower after 1993 edison spokesmen have said they believe the deal 
can be modified to placate those critics 
scecorp also announced that first quarter profits rose 46 
percent to 172 million or 79 cents a share from 118 million or 
54 cents a share a year earlier revenue rose 2 percent to 156 
billion from 153 billion 
allen said the higher profits were due almost entirely to a puc 
decision shifting some earnings to the first second and fourth 
quarters from the third quarter without affecting annual earnings 
</TEXT>
